<Content>I've only had the Zen Xtra a couple of weeks but am totally hooked on it. I was wary on buying a Creative Lab product after the Jukebox I bought 4 years ago from Creative which crashed with regularity.  This one is different, so far no problems with playing or downloading to it. The volume on this player is sufficiently improved as well.  It does have a couple of minor drawbacks but they are over shadowed by all the advantages the player has.  After downloading the newest driver and updated software it was a snap to upload music to the player.  It take less than 30 seconds an album to upload to the Zen using USB 2.  For simplicity, I'll compare the Zen Xtra to an 20 gig Ipod.<p>	Ipod 20 gig<br>25 % smaller than the Zen <br>Simple interface <br>Bauhaus design industrial white<br> <br>	Zen Xtra 40 gig<br>Twice the drive space for a LOT less  <br>WMA capability <br>Since the same quality WMA is 1/2 the size of MP3, the Zen holds 4 time more music <br>Has more sound controls<br>Has more play choices <p>User replaceable battery (what was Apple thinking!)<br>Leatherette case included <br>File drag and drop from File Explorer <br>Mass file tag editing <br>On the fly Play lists  
